social_posts.post_text: Stuffed my sugar cookie stocking with Nutella! What are you stuffing in your stocking?!
Modern gingerbread house! One of the most challenging baking projects yet! While nowhere near perfect, can’t wait to do this again next year.
Santa hat sugar cookie stuffed with Nutella for a very Merry Christmas Eve!

Fun New Year’s countdown sprinkle surprise star sugar cookies! Evie’s hand makes a debut at the end bc she couldn’t wait to play with the sprinkles!
Instructions:
Use your fav sugar cookie recipe and cut out two large stars and then a small one for the inner layer. Bake the outer layers together, these were 10 mins and the inner layer was 5 mins. 
Use icing to glue the layers together and add your fav sprinkles in the middle for fun countdown surprise!
Decorate the top with icing, edible gel and sprinkles!
Happy National pizza day!! Colossal cookie disguised as a pizza! Sugar cookie topped with coconut shreds cheese and sugar cookie pepperoni and stuffed with Nutella
Make mini heart Valentine’s sugar cookies for your Valentine without using a cookie cutter!

Fuzzy chocolate chip monster cookies for Halloween! Make any chocolate chip cookie Halloween ready by rolling it in sprinkles and adding eyes to it. I loved getting Evie involved - she helped to add the eyes into the cookies!
We’re finally settled into our new home and can’t wait to be baking more again and sharing my recipes! One of my all-time favs - Chocolate chip cookie stuffed with Nutella!

Over a year and half later, our home is completed and we’re moved in! It was truly a second full time job with site visits and scouring to finalize every last detail of a place we get to call home! Can’t wait to bake and share more recipes with you all!
Making of a glam girl sugar cookie with hot pink wayfarer sunglasses! Deliciously stuffed with Nutella.

Evie and I had some fun this weekend making the letter E out of sugar cookie dough. We made a small version and larger version, covered with sprinkles, baked and created this video! 

The smaller E is about 4 inches and took 12 minutes at 350 degrees to bake. The larger E is 10 inches and took 30 minutes at 350 degrees to bake.

Change up your chocolate chip cookies by doubling the amount of chocolate chips in your fav chocolate chip cookie recipe!

Below is my favorite recipe:

Ingredients
4 cups all-purpose flour (480 g)
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, at room temperature
1 cup white granulated sugar
1 cup dark brown sugar
2 large eggs, at room temperature
2 tsps pure vanilla extract
2 tbsp heavy cream
5 cups chocolate chips

Directions
In medium mixing bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda & salt. Set flour mixture to side
Cream together the butter and sugars for about 2-3 minutes, until the mixture is lighter in color and fluffy in texture
Reduce mixer speed to low and add in the egg, then vanilla extract & heavy cream 
Continuing with mixer on low speed, pour in the flour mixture and mix until just combined
Once the dough comes together, add chocolate chips.
Use 1 cup measuring cup to make extra large cookies!! Top cookie with more chocolate chips.
Wrap each cookies with plastic wrap and freeze/refrigerate them for at least 30 mins.
To bake, preheat oven to 350F degrees. Bake for 20-25 mins or until edges are golden-brown.
